# My Dotfiles

This repository contains my personal dotfiles and configuration files for various tools and applications. These configurations are designed to work across different machines and provide a consistent development environment.

## Features

- Shell configurations (zsh, bash)
- Git configuration and templates
- Vim configuration
- Tmux configuration
- OSX-specific settings
- Various utility scripts

## Installation

1. Clone this repository:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/yourusername/dotfiles.git ~/.dotfiles
   cd ~/.dotfiles
   ```

2. Run the installation script:
   ```bash
   ./manage.sh install
   ```

This will create symlinks for all configuration files in your home directory.

## Management

- `./manage.sh install` - Create symlinks for all configuration files
- `./manage.sh remove` - Remove all symlinks
- `./manage.sh check` - Check for broken symlinks
- `./manage.sh clean` - Remove broken symlinks

## Structure

- `zshrc` - Zsh configuration
- `vimrc` - Vim configuration
- `gitconfig` - Git configuration
- `tmux.conf` - Tmux configuration
- `osx/` - OSX-specific settings
- `config/` - Application-specific configurations
- `vim/` - Vim plugins and additional configuration

